    "focus_areas": "Energy Systems Analysis, Decarbonization Strategy, Climate and Emissions Modeling, Electrification, Energy Policy and Planning, GIS and Spatial Analysis",
    "short_bio": "Environmental engineer and climate/energy analyst with experience spanning decarbonization planning, emissions and energy modeling, and sustainability strategy. My work has focused on translating complex technical and spatial datasets into practical decision making tools for climate and energy transition planning across sectors including buildings, transportation, industry, ports, and public infrastructure. I'm especially interested in applied energy systems work at the intersection of analytics, electrification, utility planning, climate strategy, and real world implementation. I enjoy roles that combine systems thinking, quantitative analysis, and clear communication to support impactful decision making.",
    "desired_role": "I'm looking for roles focused on applied energy and climate systems analysis, decarbonization strategy, sustainability analytics, or internal climate/energy teams. I'm especially interested in positions involving energy modeling, DSM/DER analysis, electrification planning, emissions analysis, spatial analysis, or translating technical analysis into actionable strategy. Open to remote or hybrid opportunities, especially mission-driven organizations working on practical aspects of the energy transition.",
