    "bio": "Environmental engineer and climate/energy analyst with experience spanning decarbonization planning, emissions and energy modeling, and sustainability strategy. My work has focused on translating complex technical and spatial datasets into practical decision making tools for climate and energy transition planning across sectors including buildings, transportation, industry, ports, and public infrastructure. I'm especially interested in applied energy systems work at the intersection of analytics, electrification, utility planning, climate strategy, and real world implementation. I enjoy roles that combine systems thinking, quantitative analysis, and clear communication to support impactful decision making."
